In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for
4 servings), and a @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a
low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat
until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}
to taste.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and a big pinch of @salt{}. Cook, breaking up
meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Swap beef or turkey for pork.

Stir in @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, @sesame dressing{1.5%ounce},
@sweet soy glaze{2 1/2%tablespoon} (5 TBSP for 4 servings), and
@sugar{1/2%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4). (Be sure to measure the sweet soy glaze; we
sent more.) Cook until carrots are softened, pork is cooked through, and sauce
has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes} more. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tablespoon}
(2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with pork mixture and any remaining sauce
from pan. Drizzle with sweet chili mayo and sprinkle with
@crispy fried onions{1}. Serve with lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.